# Octolens

This plugin auto-configures the **Octolens MCP server** (`octolens`). Octolens is a
social-listening platform: a workspace tracks **keywords** (a brand, competitor, or
product phrase), a pipeline collects matching posts — **mentions** — from Reddit,
Twitter/X, LinkedIn, YouTube, TikTok, Bluesky, Hacker News, GitHub, news, podcasts,
and the open web, and every mention is AI-scored for relevance, sentiment, and topic
**tags**. Saved filter presets are **feeds**, which can drive notifications.

## Use the MCP first

When the Octolens MCP tools are connected (names start with `octolens` / `Octolens`),
use them directly — they are self-documenting. Typical tools: `list_mentions`,
`get_mention`, `list_keywords` / `add_keyword` / `update_keyword` / `pause_keyword` /
`delete_keyword`, `list_feeds` / `create_feed` / `update_feed`, `list_tags`,
`get_workspace`, `get_usage`, `analytics`, `search_slack_channels`,
`list_keyword_suggestions`. Read each tool's description — don't guess parameters.

If MCP isn't available, fall back to the REST API v2 (`https://app.octolens.com/api/v2`,
Bearer auth with an `ak_...` API key). See the bundled `octolens` skill for the full
endpoint catalog and filter shapes.

## Rules of engagement

- **Resolve keyword names to numeric IDs first.** The `keyword` filter is ID-only; a
  name returns a 400. Use `find_keyword` / `list_keywords` (or `GET /keywords`) before filtering.
- **Never invent values for write tools.** `add_*` / `update_*` / `create_*` / `delete_*` /
  `pause_*` mutate the live workspace. Gather every value (emails, Slack channels, webhook
  URLs, frequencies, exclude lists) from the user — don't fabricate them.
- **To wire a Slack alert:** `search_slack_channels` to get channel IDs → `create_feed`
  with a SLACK destination.
- **Summarize, don't dump.** Turn mention lists into insight: sentiment split, top
  sources/authors, volume trend.

For details (auth, mention filter syntax, gotchas, every REST endpoint), defer to the
**octolens skill** in this plugin.
